 Performance measures for three years, beginning with the year that
the project would begin, which will be used to measure the
effectiveness of the project;

 The nature of the specific export barrier and the extent to which
the proposal is likely to successfully remove, resolve, or mitigate
that barrier;

 The potential trade impact of the proposed project on market
retention, market access, and market expansion, including the
potential for expanding commercial sales in the targeted market;

 The ability of the organization to provide an experienced staff
with the requisite technical and trade experience to execute the
proposal;

 The cost of the project and the amount of other resources dedicated
to the project, including cash and goods and services of the U.S.
industry and foreign third parties;
